In exploring the temporal trends within the movie industry, the release date of movies provides a fascinating lens through which we can observe shifts in production and distribution strategies. One way to visualize this is by examining the number of movies released each year, which can reveal patterns or anomalies in the film industry.

### Visualization: Number of Movies Released Per Year

Let's delve into a timeline visualization that represents the count of movies released annually. This will help us identify peaks and troughs in movie releases, potentially correlating them with historical events, economic cycles, or changes in technology and consumer behavior.

```json
{
  "$schema": "https://vega.github.io/schema/vega-lite/v5.json",
  "description": "A line chart showing the number of movies released each year.",
  "data": {
    "url": "data/movies.json"
  },
  "transform": [
    {"calculate": "year(datum['Release Date'])", "as": "Release Year"},
    {"aggregate": [{"op": "count", "as": "Number of Movies"}], "groupby": ["Release Year"]}
  ],
  "mark": "line",
  "encoding": {
    "x": {
      "field": "Release Year",
      "type": "temporal",
      "title": "Year"
    },
    "y": {
